"{\"uid\": \"yardbarker.com-olympics-articles-us_defeats_australia_in_olympic_duel_in_the_pool_maintains_swimming_crown-s1_13132_40700746\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Team USA and its Australian counterparts always seem to deliver the competitive drama when it comes their rivalry in Olympic swimming.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 8, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9907621499379099, \"rank\": 0.009323983395598184, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 17, \"end\": 27, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9970580271224323, \"rank\": 0.0015563802511332904, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That rivalry hit a fever pitch ahead of the Paris Games, with Aussie swimmers making pointed comments about hearing the American anthem, cowbells and eventook digs at Olympic legend Michael Phelps.\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 256, \"end\": 271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"American anthem\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\"}, {\"begin\": 318, \"end\": 332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.346395349557554e-36, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But despite all the talk, the Americans demonstrated to the world why they are still the dominant swim nation.\", \"from\": 335, \"to\": 445, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA topped the total medal count (USA 28, AUS 18) and edged out Australia in golds (USA 8, AUS 7) - needing the final event of the swim program,the women's 4x100 medley relay, to snatch the victory.\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 447, \"end\": 455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9907621499379099, \"rank\": 0.009323983395598184, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 516, \"end\": 525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.7273013612722132, \"rank\": 0.21802342259971685, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you dig deeper, however, the stats show Australia is not necessarily the proverbial little brother it's been to the U.S anymore.\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 783, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 695, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.7273013612722132, \"rank\": 0.21802342259971685, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When their swimmers both appeared in individual event finals, the results were split right down the middle.\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 892, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There were eight instances of at least one Australian finishing ahead of the American swimmers and eight in the reverse.\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 1013, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 936, \"end\": 946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9970580271224323, \"rank\": 0.0015563802511332904, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 970, \"end\": 978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997251653270898, \"rank\": 0.00016441606653989192, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fascinatingly, only one man from each country won individual gold in Paris - AmericanBobby Finke in the 1500 freestyleand Australian Cameron McEvoy in the 50 freestyle.\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1084, \"end\": 1089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999993227636443, \"rank\": 6.772368673764162e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1137, \"end\": 1147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9970580271224323, \"rank\": 0.0015563802511332904, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1148, \"end\": 1162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameron_McEvoy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cameron McEvoy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameron_McEvoy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameron_McEvoy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women, on the other hand, practically dominated the top of the podium.\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1259, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Individual golds won by American or Australian women were split evenly (USA 4, AUS 4).\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1284, \"end\": 1292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997251653270898, \"rank\": 0.00016441606653989192, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1296, \"end\": 1306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9970580271224323, \"rank\": 0.0015563802511332904, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But when the two nations went head-to-head in the relay events, the Americans dominated per usual, finishing ahead of the Aussies five times compared to two.\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1505, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It'll be another four years before these two nations face off on the Olympic stage again, but the Los Angeles Games will be the perfect stage for another rematch.\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1669, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1605, \"end\": 1616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999997064344801, \"rank\": 1.3220533783357628e-07, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Austen Bundy is a journalist and sports junkie from the Washington, D. C.  area  More must-reads:  Get the latest news and rumors, customized to your favorite sports and teams.\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1704, \"end\": 1710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport\", \"score\": 0.6143095798282351, \"rank\": 0.6278387695445661, \"text\": \"sport